                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72115/3421: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 24, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. Legation Peking reports<note n="20" xml:id="d437fn20">Telegram not
                        printed.</note> that British and French Legations are urging internment of
                    all Austrians and Germans in China and liquidation of enemy property. The
                    Department has instructed Mr. Reinsch that in its opinion such questions should
                    await results of Peace Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
